sentence: Among the underlying components of the S&P 500 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Nike (Symbol: NKE), where a total of 70,940 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 7.1 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 125.2% of NKE's average daily trading volume over the past month of 5.7 million shares.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $110 strike call option expiring February 21, 2020, with 33,950 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 3.4 million underlying shares of NKE.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $235 strike call option expiring January 31, 2020, with 2,391 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 239,100 underlying shares of HD.
